To start a Ray cluster on multiple nodes via CLI, you can use the Ray cluster launcher and the Ray CLI. After defining the configuration in a YAML file, run the following command:

$ ray up -y config.yaml

You can also start a head node for the cluster using the Cluster API in Python:

cluster = Cluster(
    initialize_head=True,
    head_node_args={
        "num_cpus": 10,
    }
)

Then, you can connect to the cluster using ray.init(address=cluster.address) in your Ray script.
